Reasoning: The paper focuses on modeling and performance analysis of pull-based live streaming schemes in peer-to-peer networks. This involves network protocols, multimedia systems, distributed computing, and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
